Class SearchEngine

java.lang.Object
SearchEngine
public class SearchEngine extends Object
Represents a SearchEngine which can find instances of Strings in Files

  • Method Details

    • fileParser

      public Scanner fileParser(File f)
      Returns a Scanner which supports parsing the stoplist, docs, and queries.

      Expected time complexity is O(1).

      Parameters:
      f - a File from which to generate the scanner
      Returns:
      Scanner

    • makeStopList

      public void makeStopList()
      Builds a HashSet of String called stoplist which tells the SearchEngine what words to ignore when indexing and querying.

      Expected time complexity is O(n) where n is the total number of 'stopwords' listed in this SearchEngine's stopfile.

      See Also:
      • fileParser(java.io.File)

    • buildIndex

      public void buildIndex()
      Builds an inverted index mapping words to the documents in which they are found.

      Expected time complexity is O(n) where n is the total sum of words across all documents provided to this SearchEngine.

      See Also:
      • fileParser(java.io.File)

    • searchSingle

      public HashSet<Document> searchSingle(String word)
      Returns HashMap type Document with the documents that contain 'word'. If no documents found, returns null.

      Expected time complexity is O(1). The word either is or is not present in this SearchEngine's index.

      Parameters:
      word - an absolute URL giving the base location of the image
      Returns:
      the documents associated with this word
      See Also:
      • searchMulti(java.lang.String[],java.lang.String)

    • searchMulti

      public HashSet<Document> searchMulti(String[] words, String unsplitQuery)
      Returns HashMap type Document with the documents that contain every word in 'words'. If no documents found, returns null.

      Expected time complexity is O(n) where n is the number of words in a given query. However, average time will be near constant.

      Parameters:
      words - a String[] containing all the words in a multi-word query
      unsplitQuery - the concatenated version of 'words'
      Returns:
      the documents associated with this multi-word query
      See Also:
      • searchSingle(java.lang.String)

    • dumpIndex

      public void dumpIndex()
      Prints the contents of this SearchEngine's inverted index to support the '@@debug' pseudo query.

      Expected time complexity is O(n) where n is the number of index Keys.

    • displayDocs

      public void displayDocs(HashSet<Document> docs)
      Prints the contents of a set of documents. Supports -d flag.

      Expected time complexity is O(n) where n is number of lines in the docs

      Parameters:
      docs - HashSet of Documents to be displayed

    • queryIndex

      public void queryIndex()
      Processes all of the queries in the Document this.queries by searching for them in the inverted index.

      Expected time complexity is O(n) where n is the number of queries. Note that queries take, on average, constant time.

      See Also:
      • searchSingle(java.lang.String)
      • searchMulti(java.lang.String[],java.lang.String)

    • run

      public void run()
      Main method to run the "Search Engine." Takes note of processing time for all major operations (makeStopList, buildIndex, queryIndex).
      See Also:
